cp|8|at|I prefer the 3@c as the negative bid over a 2@h or 2@s rebid. It does very occasionally give responder an awkward problem when he has a good hand with clubs and no support for partner's suit. But even if that happens, most often the contract ends up in opener's suit anyway so no real harm is done if responder is forced to either underbid 3@c, bid 2N, or raise with 2-card support.|
