cp||at|Responder should only bid 3@c when he has no aces or kings, fewer than 6 HCP, and less than 3-card support for opener's suit. If he has a weak hand but 3+ card support he should jump to 4 of a major. Thus the auction 2@c-2@d-2@h-4@h is an example of "fast arrival" showing a weak hand with heart support. The auction 2@c-2@d-2@h-3@h shows that responder has a stronger hand with at least 1 ace or king or 6+ HCP (slow arrival) and is potentially interested in slam.|
